1":"1399–1441","1427–1480":"1427–1480","1431–1528":"1431–1528","1385–1407":"1385–1407","1385–1416":"1385–1416","1385":"1385","1473":"1473","ABT 1402":"about 1402","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","14 Jul 1473":"23 July 1473","1448":"1448","1404":"1404","1402":"1402","about 1426":"about 1426","1444":"1444","Abt 1431":"about 1431","1399":"1399","1431":"1431","1441":"1441","about 1400":"about 1400","1407":"1407","1528":"1528","1416":"1416","1427":"1427","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Great Cokesay, Worchestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","Drayton, Oxfordshire, England":"Drayton, Oxfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Joyce","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Apparently from the Norman male name <i>Josce</i> (Middle English <i>Josse</i>), which in turn is from <i>Jodocus</i>, a Latinized form of a Breton name, <i>Iodoc</i>, meaning ‘lord’, borne by a 7th-century Breton saint. The name was in use in England among Breton followers of William the Conqueror. However, although this was fairly common as a male given name in the Middle Ages, it had virtually died out by the 14th century. There is evidence of its use as a girl's name from the 16th century onwards in parishes with strong Puritan links, which suggests that it may have been associated with the vocabulary word <i>joy</i>;  see  Joy .  It was strongly revived in the 19th century under the influence of popular fiction. It is borne by characters in Mrs  Henry Wood's  East Lynne (  1861 ) and  Edna Lyall's  In the Golden Days (  1885 ). Modern use may well have been influenced also by the common Irish surname derived from the medieval Norman male name.  See also  Joss ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Joyce Cokesay was born about 1402, in Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Walter Cokesey, was 18 and her mother, Isabel de Harcourt, was 18. She married John Greville about 1426. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 23 July 1473, at the age of 72."},"et":{"ABT 1402–14 Jul 1473":"umbes 1402–23. juuli 1473","1402–1473":"1402–1473","1404–1448":"1404–1448","1380–1444":"1380–1444","1399–1441":"1399–1441","1427–1480":"1427–1480","1431–1528":"1431–1528","1385–1407":"1385–1407","1385–1416":"1385–1416","1385":"1385","1473":"1473","ABT 1402":"umbes 1402","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","14 Jul 1473":"23. juuli 1473","1448":"1448","1404":"1404","1402":"1402","about 1426":"umbes 1426","1444":"1444","Abt 1431":"umbes 1431","1399":"1399","1431":"1431","1441":"1441","about 1400":"umbes 1400","1407":"1407","1528":"1528","1416":"1416","1427":"1427","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Great Cokesay, Worchestershire, England":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Drayton, Oxfordshire, England":"Drayton, Oxfordshire, England"},"fi":{"ABT 1402–14 Jul 1473":"noin 1402–23. heinäkuuta 1473","1402–1473":"1402–1473","1404–1448":"1404–1448","1380–1444":"1380–1444","1399–1441":"1399–1441","1427–1480":"1427–1480","1431–1528":"1431–1528","1385–1407":"1385–1407","1385–1416":"1385–1416","1385":"1385","1473":"1473","ABT 1402":"noin 1402","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","14 Jul 1473":"23. heinäkuuta 1473","1448":"1448","1404":"1404","1402":"1402","about 1426":"noin 1426","1444":"1444","Abt 1431":"noin 1431","1399":"1399","1431":"1431","1441":"1441","about 1400":"noin 1400","1407":"1407","1528":"1528","1416":"1416","1427":"1427","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Great Cokesay, Worchestershire, England":"Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Drayton, Oxfordshire, England":"Drayton, Oxfordshire, England"},"fr":{"ABT 1402–14 Jul 1473":"environ 1402–23 juillet 1473","1402–1473":"1402–1473","1404–1448":"1404–1448","1380–1444":"1380–1444","1399–1441":"1399–1441","1427–1480":"1427–1480","1431–1528":"1431–1528","1385–1407":"1385–1407","1385–1416":"1385–1416","1385":"1385","1473":"1473","ABT 1402":"en